  "text": "The remaining patients studied were referred for genetic analysis by clinicians who had diagnosed their PHA1. A blood sample for DNA analysis was obtained from each index patient and their immediate family members after they provided informed consent, in accordance with institutional review board approved protocols, and genomic DNA was extracted as described previously [CITATION_1] . Sequence variants were detected as described previously [CITATION_2] . Briefly, coding exons and their flanking intronic regions of MR were amplified using previously described primers (5) and were analyzed using denaturing HPLC (DHPLC) as described previously [CITATION_3] . The identified mutations were not observed by DHPLC in 90 control individuals whose DNA had been referred to our laboratory for evaluation of other genetic diseases; these individuals were primarily American of Caucasian descent with a small number of Hispanic Americans as well. RNA was isolated, and cDNA was prepared from patients' leukocytes as described previously [CITATION_4] . cDNA was prepared and sequenced by standard methods.",
